{"TopicId":102277,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.8] PersistentRotation 1.8.6","CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-19T21:24:41Z","PageNum":15,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-25T21:45:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003ENew Version Released!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ENow with 1.1.3 support and new GUI structure!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EThere still is a lot to be done. I am not sure wether I will continue developing this mod yet.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EEDIT: Just read your request concerning PluginData, stand by for patch.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EEDIT2: \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003ENew Version Released!\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EPersistentRotation now saves to PluginData. Enjoy!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-25T22:43:49Z\u0022 title=\u002206/25/2016 10:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MarkusA380\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T00:16:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I was playing 1.1.2 without it and its just weird. Glad to be reinstalling!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T08:49:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222647532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466900194\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I was playing 1.1.2 without it and its just weird. Glad to be reinstalling!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI truly hope you\u0027re happy with it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T09:34:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, so PR is currently storing all cfgs in KSPpath\\PluginData. Do you want it to be stored in GameData\\PersistentRotation\\PluginData or is it (as I thought) better like this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"evileye.x","CreatedById":153755,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T09:39:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222647382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466891121\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003ENew Version Released!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ENow with 1.1.3 support and new GUI structure!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EThere still is a lot to be done. I am not sure wether I will continue developing this mod yet.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EEDIT: Just read your request concerning PluginData, stand by for patch.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EEDIT2: \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003ENew Version Released!\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EPersistentRotation now saves to PluginData. Enjoy!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour mod is a savior for all of us who wants to have somewhat realistic craft behavior without magic RW, thank you so much!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T10:44:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222647978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466933975\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022evileye.x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, evileye.x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour mod is a savior for all of us who wants to have somewhat realistic craft behavior without magic RW, thank you so much!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry but what do you mean with magic RW?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T11:40:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/45759-markusa380/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002245759\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/45759-markusa380/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@MarkusA380\u003C/a\u003EIs it normal that PR is storing the data inside the \u0022KSPRoot/PluginData/PersistentRotation\u0022 folder instead of the \u0022KSPRoot/GameData/PersistentRotation/PluginData/PersistentRotation\u0022 folder?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: IIRC the old \u0022KSPRoot\u0022 folders are considered \u0022legacy\u0022 since 0.18 or so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-26T11:51:05Z\u0022 title=\u002206/26/2016 11:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Phineas Freak\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"evileye.x","CreatedById":153755,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T11:42:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222648030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466937882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry but what do you mean with magic RW?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReaction wheels.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-26T12:25:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHotfix released!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222648079\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466941335\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022evileye.x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, evileye.x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReaction wheels.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh yes. Thanks for those nice words. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Unknown Venom","CreatedById":160794,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T10:29:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello Mark this is Gauration... ugh I wish I knew how to change meh username! ohwell... nice mod!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"acc","CreatedById":80018,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T22:38:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoes a working version for 1.1.2 exist? I tried latest pre-1.1.3 (which is 1.0.2), but did\u0027nt work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncan\u0027t update yet to 1.1.3, because \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E/RP-0 not ready yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T04:26:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222647976\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466933673\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn June 26, 2016 at 5:34 AM, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, so PR is currently storing all cfgs in KSPpath\\PluginData. Do you want it to be stored in GameData\\PersistentRotation\\PluginData or is it (as I thought) better like this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit will work either way, but the more standard way of doing things these days would be the second option, as mentioned the PluginData folder in the main KSP directory is mainly legacy. Ppl looking for the config files wouldn\u0027t expect to find them there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealGecko","CreatedById":162682,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T08:12:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E still does not show PR as compatible with 1.1.3. Is it \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T10:46:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651193\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467101528\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162682\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealGecko\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RealGecko said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E still does not show PR as compatible with 1.1.3. Is it \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it is. I\u0027ve opened an issue on their Github tracker, this should be fixed sooner or later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealGecko","CreatedById":162682,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T10:47:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651278\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467110792\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it is. I\u0027ve opened an issue on their Github tracker, this should be fixed sooner or later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, man!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"evileye.x","CreatedById":153755,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T12:20:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/45759-markusa380/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002245759\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/45759-markusa380/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MarkusA380\u003C/a\u003E. I have a humble request.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you make insta-stabization on warp when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E enabled optional?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFeels like little bit cheating, the same as stock warp rotation cheat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Sometimes you can have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, but no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E or torque for stabilisation.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be great for \u0022realistic KSP\u0022 crowd.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T16:10:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651359\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467116429\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022evileye.x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, evileye.x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/45759-markusa380/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002245759\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/45759-markusa380/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@MarkusA380\u003C/a\u003E. I have a humble request.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you make insta-stabization on warp when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E enabled optional?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFeels like little bit cheating, the same as stock warp rotation cheat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Sometimes you can have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, but no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E or torque for stabilisation.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be great for \u0022realistic KSP\u0022 crowd.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve already thought about it. But I am yet unsure on how to do it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShould it just continue rotating even though \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is enabled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is also similar to the problem wether the reference rotation mode should consume electric energy and monopropellant.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just think that for both of these you can\u0027t have a solution everyone likes...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"evileye.x","CreatedById":153755,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T16:23:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467130204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShould it just continue rotating even though \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is enabled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsider it\u0027s like stock behavior - \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t hold prograde/retrograde during timewarp, does it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467130204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just think that for both of these you can\u0027t have a solution everyone likes...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly, that\u0027s why we all love options and configs \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0We all do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"leudaimon","CreatedById":153781,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T16:44:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467130204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve already thought about it. But I am yet unsure on how to do it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoincidentally this discussion appeared yesterday in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E irc channel. A nice suggestion that (I think \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0made) was to have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E in time warp stopping rotation only if angular momentum is below some threshold. Above that, and the behaviour would be similar to the current when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is disabled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI myself often forget to deactivate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E before separation\u00A0when I have an uncontrolled spin-stabilized probe, and end up unable to time warp, which commonly dooms the mission. Thus, besides the \u0022cheating\u0022 component, there is also a gameplay aspect that is important.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T19:32:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651736\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467132291\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153781\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022leudaimon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, leudaimon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoincidentally this discussion appeared yesterday in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E irc channel. A nice suggestion that (I think \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0made) was to have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in time warp stopping rotation only if angular momentum is below some threshold. Above that, and the behaviour would be similar to the current when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is disabled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI myself often forget to deactivate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E before separation\u00A0when I have an uncontrolled spin-stabilized probe, and end up unable to time warp, which commonly dooms the mission. Thus, besides the \u0022cheating\u0022 component, there is also a gameplay aspect that is important.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a good idea! Will do so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651718\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467130995\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022evileye.x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, evileye.x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly, that\u0027s why we all love options and configs \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0We all do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah well but I honestly don\u0027t want to write this code tree. Sorry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T20:04:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E1.4 released!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222651736\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467132291\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153781\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022leudaimon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, leudaimon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[...] A nice suggestion that (I think \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0made) was to have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in time warp stopping rotation only if angular momentum is below some threshold. Above that, and the behaviour would be similar to the current when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is disabled. [...]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is now a feature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, the mod *should* be alot more resource friendly and maybe even more stable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-28T20:04:55Z\u0022 title=\u002206/28/2016 08:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MarkusA380\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"leudaimon","CreatedById":153781,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T21:58:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222652033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467144276\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.4 released!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool! Do you know if this version is compatible with 1.1.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T23:14:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222652221\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467151137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153781\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022leudaimon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, leudaimon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool! Do you know if this version is compatible with 1.1.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think so. Why should it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"leudaimon","CreatedById":153781,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-28T23:15:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222652326\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467155656\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy should it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E/RP-0 are not 1.1.3 compatible yet. But it\u0027s great news that Persistent rotation is totally updated and improved. I\u0027ll be waiting for the complete update of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E suite before moving to 1.1.3 though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-29T07:29:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153781-leudaimon/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022153781\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/153781-leudaimon/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@leudaimon\u003C/a\u003Eyou can download the dev version of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E and use the current release of RP-0 if you want. 99% of these two mods are just \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}